<title>USA: ECI Telecom completes $100 mln placement.</title>
<headline>ECI Telecom completes $100 mln placement.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>ECI Telecom Ltd said Thursday it completed a $100 million private placement of 4.50 percent seven-year convertible subordinated notes.</p>
<p>The notes are convertible into ECI Telecom's ordinary shares at $25 per share six months after closing, the company said, adding that it will use the proceeds as working capital.</p>
<p>The company said that of the $100 million in notes, it issued $40 million to Clal Electronics Industries Ltd, $45 million an affiliate of the Charles Rosner Bronfman Trust and $15 million to the Renaissance Fund.</p>
<p>ECI's stock closed Tuesday at 21-1/4.</p>
